So my New Year’s resolution was basically starting from scratch and letting go. In my case it was about the entire closet I left at a storage in NY during the pandemic without hopes of getting it back any time soon. Thanks to @roadwaymoving in a matter of 48 hrs they managed to come up with the perfect solution for that without me actually having to be physically in NY. Their customer service was so on top of making sure everything was being received and taken care of, I didn’t expect to receive the shipment so soon - it was quite the surprise they actually arrived on December 31st. What a way to start the New Year! Doesn’t mean I’m moving anywhere but after 2 years of paying for a storage, I knew I couldn’t keep my clothes in there any longer and needed to find a solution to getting them back. I’m letting go, donating and selling probably 80% of that closet because I don’t need any more clothes, I really just need to feel lighter this year.

Thank you @roadwaymoving for making my number one new year’s resolution possible. I highly suggest their service to anyone in need of a short or long distance move. As a little treat, here’s a code you can use for a discount on your next move “MarianaC10” 💕🤍

#happynewyear #newyear #2023 #roadwaymoving #2023resolutions #2023mood

Literalmente jugando con mi vida porque no soy muy de seguir las reglas. Estar descalza, sin montura, a pelo, y sujetándome de la poquita crin de caballo, confiando en él, pero cada vez confiando un poquito más en mi. Me viene lo cursi, pero los dos corrimos con esa libertad en el mar como si no hubiera un solo pensamiento en mi mente más que el estar presente y el confiar… y a mí, esa sonrisita nadie me la quita. ¿Cuántas veces tememos hacer ciertas cosas por el miedo de fracasar o de caernos? A mi me pasa a cada rato. Y estos son los pequeños recordatorios que me hacen darme cuenta que el confiar aún así sin tener de dónde sujetarme harán que no me caiga. El confiar con el corazón y con la pasión son las herramientas más fuertes que tenemos. Ese día me levante con tantas ganas de soltar las riendas y dejar que el caballo me llevará a donde él quería, y vaya que a los dos nos hacía mucha falta. 

Ya luego nos pusimos la montura para seguirle un ratito más con precaución porque ya había gente caminando por la playa. Y eso que eran las 8 am. 

(Aunque monto seguido, cabe mencionar que mis piernas terminaron como spaghetti y estuve bastante adolorida los días siguientes pero ese sentimiento no lo cambio por nada 🤍🫶🏼) don’t try this at home kids… cuidado con aquellos que no saben manejar bien a un caballo, porque el montar a pelo no es tan fácil como se ve. Luego no quiero accidentes por mi culpa 🫣

My June in a nutshell: summer hits different for me this year🎢 Just getting off the hormonal ride and I’m just soooo happy and grateful I was able to egg freeze💉🥚- most importantly have the freedom to decide for myself and take the reins of my future. I don’t believe it will ever be an easy decision/process for any woman, but it’s surely a brave one and that comes with a lot of reward. I definitely feel stronger. 

I’m sure no one loves medical visits, but this was a bit of a game changer for me. With its holistic approach @clinicafi was exactly what I needed - they made my process feel easy breezy, and exciting (I also got one of the best massages ever 🧖🏽‍♀️).

Here’s some behind the scenes of what my last 3 weeks looked like. Last photo was after the egg extraction. Bloating was just getting real…

Special thanks to all the wonderful staff at @clinicafi, Pau, Maggie, Xime, Sofi, Dra. Debbie, Dra. Sofía and Dr. Gutierrez for taking such good care of me and my tummy ❤️🍳 

Also, big thanks to @fermedina for being the best roomie/emotional support 🫶🏼 and to my friends for all the love, surprise visits, sweets and flowers🪄🌹🍭 I’m glad I was never alone ✨

The Q&A I promised is coming soon, and also a tour of the clinic. Stay tuned 🤍

Ps. If someone visits @clinicafi in CDMX make sure to mention “MARIANA10” for a special discount!
